        "description": {
            "value": "<p>As a swashbuckler, you have your own distinctive style that enables you to gracefully handle everyday events and life-or-death situations alike. Choose a swashbuckler's style. This style determines the additional actions you use to gain panache and makes you trained in the skill related to that action.</p>\n<p>You move carefully, feinting and creating false openings to lead your foes into inopportune attacks.</p>\n<p>You are trained in Deception. You gain @Compendium[pf2e.classfeatures.Panache]{Panache} during an encounter whenever you successfully @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Feint]{Feint} or @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Create a Diversion]{Create a Diversion} against a foe.</p>"
